        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 7:26PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 723 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a thunderstorm that were
generally weakening, but producing strong wind gusts to around 50
mph. Only light precipitation and little thunder is expected but
strong winds may produce blowing dust and areas of reduced
visibility with localized gusts in excess of 50 mph possible.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Great Falls, Helena, Cascade, East Helena, Fairfield, Dutton, Fort
Shaw, Augusta, Black Eagle, Wolf Creek, Fort Shaw, Power, York,
Spring Meadow Lake State Park, Eden, Stockett, First Peoples Buffalo
Jump State Park, Ulm, Simms, and Portage.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
